The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Feb. 24: The high court today rapped Government Railway Police (GRP) for its callousness in probing the death of a Kharagpur businessman.

 Sheikh Safiul was allegedly beaten up severely by Railway Protection Force (RPF) jawans who picked him up on May 5 last year. A division bench of Chief Justice V.S. Sirpurkar and Justice A.K. Ganguly has summoned the GRPs Kharagpur superinten-dent next Friday to explain why a murder charge was not pressed against the RPF personnel.

 Calcutta: Pankaj Banerjee, the leader of Opposition in the Assembly, has been shifted to the ICU of a private hospital where he was admitted following a heart attack. The Trinamul Congress MLA from Tollygunge was hospitalised on Thursday.

 Calcutta: Municipal affairs minister Asok Bhattacharya took a dig at health minister Surjya Kanta Mishra on Friday saying that munici-pal healthcare units and maternity centres were providing better service than many hospitals. Mishra announced a Rs 58.3-crore health programme for 63 municipalities across the state.

 Calcutta: The life sentences of Ashim Chakraborty and his mother Swapna Chakraborty, awarded by a trial court for killing Ashims wife Rumi, has been upheld by the high court. Ashim, a resident of Burdwan town, who got married in 1992, killed his wife and set her on fire two years later.




